# Set knitr options to continue on error
knitr::opts_chunk$set(error = TRUE)

# imports
pacman::p_load(
  tidyverse,
  Applr
)

# Set seed for reproducibility
set.seed(123)

# Number of observations
n <- 50

# Generate predictor variables
x <- runif(n, -10, 10)
x_pos <- runif(n, 0, 10)
x_neg <- runif(n, -10, 0)
x_switch <- sample(c(0, 1, 2), n, replace = TRUE)

Models

x variations

y ~ x

# Model definition
y.single <- x
lm.single <- lm(y.single ~ x)

# lm_equation
lm_equation(lm.single)
## [1] "y.single = 6.28e-17 + 1*x"
# Base R plot with abline
plot(x, y.single, main = "Single Predictor: y ~ x", 
     xlab = "x", ylab = "y", pch = 19, col = "steelblue")
abline(lm.single, col = "red", lwd = 2)

# Base R plot with add_slice_2d
plot(x, y.single, main = "Single Predictor: y ~ x", 
     xlab = "x", ylab = "y", pch = 19, col = "steelblue")
add_slice_2d(lm.single)
## X-axis not specified; used first x variable as x-axis: Use xaxis="var_name"
## Error in data.frame(..., check.names = FALSE): arguments imply differing number of rows: 100, 0
# slice_2d
slice_2d(lm.single)
## Warning in slice_2d(lm.single): X-axis not specified; used first x variable as
## x-axis: Use xaxis="var_name"
## Error in data.frame(..., check.names = FALSE): arguments imply differing number of rows: 100, 0
# drawit
drawit(lm.single, xaxis = "x")

# ggplot with geom_slice
ggplot(data.frame(x, y.single), aes(x, y.single)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_slice(lm.single)

y ~ x + x_pos

# Model definition
y.add <- x + x_pos
lm.add <- lm(y.add ~ x + x_pos)

# lm_equation
lm_equation(lm.add)
## [1] "y.add = -3.39e-15 + 1*x + 1*x_pos"
# Base R plot with fitted values
plot(x, y.add, main = "Additive: y ~ x + x_pos", 
     xlab = "x", ylab = "y", pch = 19, col = "steelblue")
points(x, fitted(lm.add), col = "red", pch = 19, cex = 0.5)

# Base R plot with add_slice_2d
plot(x, y.add, main = "Additive: y ~ x + x_pos", 
     xlab = "x", ylab = "y", pch = 19, col = "steelblue")
add_slice_2d(lm.add)
## X-axis not specified; used first x variable as x-axis: Use xaxis="var_name"
## Slice value not specified - Used mean of x_pos

# slice_2d
slice_2d(lm.add)
## Warning in slice_2d(lm.add): X-axis not specified; used first x variable as
## x-axis: Use xaxis="var_name"
## Slice value not specified - Used mean of x_pos

# drawit
drawit(lm.add, xaxis = "x")
## Warning in drawit(lm.add, xaxis = "x"): x_pos value not specified; enter value
## between:0.00624773325398564-9.84956979984418
# ggplot with geom_slice
ggplot(data.frame(x, y.add), aes(x, y.add)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_slice(lm.add) +
  geom_slice(lm.add, predict_vars = list(x_pos = 0.007))

y ~ x + I(x^2)

# Model definition
y.quadratic <- x + x^2
lm.quadratic <- lm(y.quadratic ~ x + I(x^2))

# lm_equation
lm_equation(lm.quadratic)
## [1] "y.quadratic = 8.29e-15 + 1*x + 1*I(x^2)"
# Base R plot with manual prediction
plot(x, y.quadratic, main = "Quadratic: y ~ x + I(x^2)", 
     xlab = "x", ylab = "y", pch = 19, col = "steelblue")
x_seq <- seq(min(x), max(x), length.out = 100)
pred <- predict(lm.quadratic, newdata = data.frame(x = x_seq))
lines(x_seq, pred, col = "red", lwd = 2)

# Base R plot with add_slice_2d

     xlab = "x", ylab = "y", pch = 19, col = "steelblue")
